TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bali, Turan G.
AU  - Cakici, Nusret
AU  - Whitelaw, Robert F.
T1  - Hybrid Tail Risk and Expected Stock Returns: When Does the Tail Wag the Dog?
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/rau006
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 4
IS  - 2
SP  - 206
EP  - 246
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We introduce a new hybrid measure of stock return tail covariance risk, motivated by the underdiversified portfolio holdings of individual investors, and investigate its cross-sectional predictive power. Our key innovation is that this covariance is measured across the left tail states of the individual stock return distribution, and not across those of the market return as in standard systematic risk measures. We document a positive and significant relation between hybrid tail covariance risk (H-TCR) and expected stock returns, with an annualized premium of 9%, in contrast to the insignificant or negative results for purely stock-specific or systematic tail risk measures. (JEL G10, G11, C13)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/rau006
ER  - 



